    "In the following analyses we present the p-values resulting from the analysis, the effect sizes are available at: https://github.",
    "com/epfl-ml4ed/relex/tree/main/docs/effect-sizes.pdf.",
    "In a first preparatory step, we verified the randomization by checking for differences between the five groups at the beginning of the study.",
    "A Kruskal-Wallis test foot_8 confirmed that there were no differences in participants' procedural writing skills as measured by their quality scores T y (pr e) (see \"Measures and Analysis\") achieved on the pretest task (χ 2 (4) = 4.85, p =.30).",
    "For the pre-survey, we obtained the construct score by averaging the items in each construct (all factor loadings were greater than 0.7) and found no significant differences either in participants' previous experience with documenting cooking recipes (χ 2 (4) = 4.83, p =.30) and attitudes towards technology (χ 2 (4) = 4.2, p =.37)."
